  LETTER #1 — Buyer Interest Letter
When to Send: Day 1, when you book the listing appointment (before you even meet with the seller)
Derived From: Jimmy Mackin (appointment-based activation, neighborhood appointment sales letter)
Mail To: 100-300 neighbors surrounding the listing


[Date]
Dear [Neighborhood] Neighbor,

I hope this letter finds you well. I’m reaching out because I’m currently working with several qualified buyers who are specifically looking for homes in [Neighborhood Name].

My buyers are pre-approved and actively searching for a [Number]-bedroom home in the [Price Range] range. They’ve told me they love your neighborhood because of [specific feature: the tree-lined streets / the proximity to excellent schools / the sense of community / etc.], and they are ready to move quickly for the right home.

I wanted to reach out to you directly because the best homes in a neighborhood like yours often sell before they ever hit the public market. If you have considered selling your home — even casually — I would love the opportunity to have a brief, no-pressure conversation about what your home might be worth in today’s market.

You may also know a friend, family member, or neighbor who has mentioned thinking about a move. If so, I would be incredibly grateful for an introduction. A quick call or text is all it takes to get the conversation started.

I’ve enclosed a brief snapshot of recent activity in [Neighborhood Name] so you can see what homes like yours are selling for. Your home’s value may surprise you.

Please don’t hesitate to reach out. I’m happy to provide a complimentary, no-obligation market analysis of your property at any time.

Warm regards,
[Agent Name]
[Company Name]
[Phone Number]
[Email Address]
[Website URL]


Customization Notes: Personalize the buyer description to match the neighborhood (beds, baths, price range, features). Attach a one-page market snapshot showing 2-3 recent comparable sales. Bring any responses to your listing appointment as proof of buyer demand (Mackin’s key tactic).

  LETTER #2 — Coming Soon Neighborhood Announcement
When to Send: Days 6-7 of Pre-Listing Phase (with your first postcard drop, about 1 week before MLS launch)
Derived From: Tom Ferry (domination campaign), Meredith Fogle (300-postcard Coming Soon), Jimmy Mackin (exclusivity)
Mail To: 100-300 neighbors surrounding the listing


[Date]
Dear [Neighborhood] Neighbor,

I wanted you to be among the first to know — your neighbor’s home at [Property Address] is preparing to come on the market, and I promised the sellers I would share the news with the neighborhood before it goes public.

Here are a few details about the home:

Address: [Full Address]
Bedrooms / Bathrooms: [X Beds / X Baths]
Square Footage: [X,XXX sq ft]
Key Features: [Updated kitchen, pool, mountain views, etc.]
Expected Price Range: [$XXX,XXX - $XXX,XXX]
Official Launch Date: [Date]

As a neighbor, you have an opportunity to preview this home before the general public. I am hosting an Exclusive Neighborhood Preview on [Date] from [Time]. You and your guests are welcome to attend.

You may know someone who has been waiting for the right home in your neighborhood. Great homes in [Neighborhood Name] don’t come along every day, so please share this with anyone who might be interested.

Curious about your own home’s value? Activity in your neighborhood directly impacts what your home is worth. I’d be happy to prepare a complimentary, no-obligation market analysis for you. Simply call, text, or email me — it only takes a few minutes.

Warm regards,
[Agent Name]
[Company Name]
[Phone Number]
[Email Address]
[Website URL]


Customization Notes: This letter pairs perfectly with a professional postcard or flyer featuring a hero photo of the property. The preview open house Evite (Fogle) should also go out at the same time via email. Emphasize exclusivity — neighbors feel special getting first access.

  LETTER #3 — Just Listed Neighborhood Letter
When to Send: Launch Day (Day 15) — mail with Direct Mail Drop #3
Derived From: Tom Ferry (domination campaign), Meredith Fogle (On Market 300 postcards), Jimmy Burgess (Thursday launch)
Mail To: 100-300 neighbors surrounding the listing


[Date]
Dear [Neighborhood] Neighbor,

I’m excited to share that your neighbor’s home at [Property Address] is now officially on the market and already generating significant interest.

During the exclusive Coming Soon period, we received [X] inquiries and [X] showing requests — a strong indication that buyers are actively looking in [Neighborhood Name]. This kind of demand is great news for every homeowner in the area.

The home is listed at [$XXX,XXX] and features [key highlight: a stunning remodeled kitchen / breathtaking backyard / etc.]. You can view the full listing, professional photos, and a virtual tour at [Listing URL or QR code reference].

You’re invited to the Grand Open House: [Date] from [Time]. Stop by to see the home, enjoy refreshments, and learn about what’s happening in the [Neighborhood Name] real estate market. Feel free to bring friends or family who may be interested in the area.

What does this mean for your home? Every home that sells in your neighborhood establishes a new data point for your property’s value. Based on current market conditions and buyer demand, homes in [Neighborhood Name] are in a very strong position. If you’ve been curious about what your home might be worth today, I’d love to put together a detailed analysis for you — no cost, no obligation, no pressure.

Just give me a call, send a text, or reply to this letter. I’m always happy to help.

Warm regards,
[Agent Name]
[Company Name]
[Phone Number]
[Email Address]
[Website URL]


Customization Notes: Include a professional property photo (exterior or hero shot). Reference specific Coming Soon interest numbers to create social proof and urgency. The QR code linking to the virtual tour (Fogle) is highly effective on this letter.

  LETTER #4 — The Magic Buyer Letter
When to Send: Pending Phase — within 48 hours of going under contract
Derived From: Meredith Fogle (Magic Buyer Letter — highest response rate of any direct mail piece)
Mail To: 100-300 neighbors surrounding the listing


[Date]
Dear [Neighborhood] Neighbor,

I recently listed your neighbor’s home at [Property Address] and it went under contract with [X] offers. The demand for homes in [Neighborhood Name] has been truly remarkable.

Here is why I’m writing to you directly: I am currently working with a qualified, pre-approved buyer who fell in love with your neighborhood during the showing process for [Property Address]. Unfortunately, they were not the winning offer — and they are still actively looking.

My buyer is specifically searching for:

Home Type: [X bedrooms, X bathrooms, single-story/two-story]
Budget: [Pre-approved up to $XXX,XXX]
Timeline: [Ready to close in 30-45 days / flexible on timing]
What They Love About Your Neighborhood: [The schools, the walkability, the lot sizes, the community feel, etc.]

If you have ever considered selling your home — even if you’re just curious about what it might be worth — this is an extraordinary opportunity. Having a motivated, pre-approved buyer already in love with your neighborhood means you could potentially sell quickly, at a strong price, and on your timeline.

There is absolutely no obligation. A quick phone call is all it takes for me to share more details and, if you’re interested, schedule a private walk-through of your home to see if it could be the right fit.

Please call or text me directly at [Phone Number]. I’m available evenings and weekends.

Warm regards,
[Agent Name]
[Company Name]
[Phone Number]
[Email Address]
[Website URL]


Customization Notes: This is Fogle’s highest-converting letter. The key is specificity — describe a REAL buyer with real criteria. If you had multiple unsuccessful offers, you have multiple Magic Buyer Letters to send. Customize the buyer description for each. This letter works because it presents a tangible, real person, not a generic solicitation.

  LETTER #5 — Just Sold Neighborhood Letter
When to Send: Within 48 hours of closing — this is your single highest-ROI letter for generating the next listing
Derived From: Tom Ferry (domination campaign #6), Jimmy Burgess (post-sale door knocking), Meredith Fogle (Sold Phase 300 postcards)
Mail To: 100-300 neighbors surrounding the listing


[Date]
Dear [Neighborhood] Neighbor,

I’m pleased to share some exciting news from your neighborhood. The home at [Property Address] has officially SOLD, and the results speak volumes about the strength of the [Neighborhood Name] real estate market.

Here are the details:

Listed At: [$XXX,XXX]
Sold At: [$XXX,XXX]
Difference: [X% over / at / under asking price]
Days on Market: [X days]
Total Showings: [X showings]
Number of Offers: [X offers received]

What does this mean for you? Every home sale in [Neighborhood Name] directly affects your property’s value. Based on this sale and current market conditions, homes in your neighborhood are performing exceptionally well. Buyer demand remains strong, inventory is limited, and the conditions are highly favorable for sellers.

I put together a comprehensive marketing plan for this home that included professional photography, video tours, targeted digital advertising, direct mail, neighborhood outreach, and open houses that attracted over [X] visitors. The sellers were thrilled with the process and the result. I would love the opportunity to do the same for you.

If you are curious about what your home is worth in today’s market, I invite you to contact me for a complimentary, no-obligation Home Value Analysis. It takes just a few minutes of your time, and the number may pleasantly surprise you.

Call or text me at [Phone Number] or visit [Website/Landing Page URL] for an instant estimate.

Warm regards,
[Agent Name]
[Company Name]
[Phone Number]
[Email Address]
[Website URL]


Customization Notes: Include the sold results prominently — numbers create credibility. If you sold over asking or received multiple offers, lead with that. Pair this letter with the 100 door hangers and Seller Seminar invitation (Letter #6). Burgess recommends also bringing a printed Seller’s Guide when door knocking with this letter.

  LETTER #6 — Seller Seminar Invitation
When to Send: 1-2 weeks after closing — the final touch that converts neighborhood awareness into listing appointments at scale
Derived From: Meredith Fogle (Sold Phase: 100 door hangers with Seller Seminar invite), Tom Ferry (geographic farming events)
Mail To: 100-300 neighbors surrounding the listing


[Date]
Dear [Neighborhood] Neighbor,

You may have noticed the recent sale of [Property Address] in your neighborhood. As the agent who marketed and sold that home, I’ve been fielding a lot of questions from homeowners in [Neighborhood Name] about what the market looks like right now and what their homes might be worth.

To answer those questions, I’m hosting a free Neighborhood Market Update & Seller Workshop exclusively for [Neighborhood Name] homeowners:

Date: [Date]
Time: [Time, e.g., 6:00 PM - 7:30 PM]
Location: [Venue — local restaurant, community center, your office, or virtual via Zoom]
Refreshments: Complimentary appetizers and beverages provided

During this casual, no-pressure session, I’ll cover:

✓  What homes in [Neighborhood Name] are selling for right now (with real data)
✓  How recent sales — including [Property Address] — impact YOUR home’s value
✓  The top 5 things sellers are doing right now to get top dollar
✓  How to prepare your home for sale without overspending
✓  Market trends and what to expect over the next 6-12 months

There is no cost and absolutely no obligation. Whether you’re thinking about selling this year, next year, or simply want to know what’s happening in your neighborhood, you’re welcome to attend.

Space is limited. Please RSVP by [RSVP Date] by calling or texting [Phone Number] or visiting [RSVP Link / Landing Page].

I look forward to seeing you there.

Warm regards,
[Agent Name]
[Company Name]
[Phone Number]
[Email Address]
[Website URL]


Customization Notes: This letter pairs with Fogle’s 100 door hangers. Print the invite on the door hanger and hand-deliver to 100 homes nearest the sold listing. For the seminar itself, prepare a 20-minute presentation with neighborhood market data, then open for Q&A. Collect contact info from every attendee. Offer complimentary CMAs to everyone who attends. This one event can generate 3-5 listing appointments.
